<HEADLINE>
FASHION SNIPPETS
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) &HT;    c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The hottest colors at the Oscars were lilac, silver, gold and
black, paired with a bared back.
</P>
<P>
   Oscar hair? It's back up in fancy 'dos or long with loose curls.
Hair sparkles were out, but tiaras are still in. But those 'N Sync
guys sported the youthful trend of brightly dyed locks in red and
blue.
</P>
<P>
   Diamonds were everywhere, on loan from famous jewelers Asprey &AMP;
Garrard, Bulgari and, of course, Harry Winston. But the Pamela
Dennis gown covered with 2,000 Lazare diamonds worn by talk-show
diva Leeza Gibbons was the biggest dazzler.
</P>
<P>
   In the men's department, the big sparkler was ``Green Mile''
star Michael Clarke Duncan, who wore huge diamond studs plus a
Concord wrist watch with a diamond-covered mouse on top.
</P>
<P>
   In spite of rumors about women in pants, only a few wore them,
including Best Actress nominees Meryl Streep and Janet McTeer.
</P>
<P>
   Fashion police Joan Rivers looked smashing in her Vera Wang
purple gown, but daughter Melissa missed the boat in a two-piece
that looked so last year. Also wearing purple were several TV
commentators, including Steven Cojocaru, who wore a white Richard
Tyler suit with a purple shirt and scarf.!end!
</P>
</TEXT>
