<SLUG> BC-BBA-RANGERS-COOKIE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
 
Ruben Mateo turns cookie monster at plate with diet rich in chips 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By T.R. SULLIVAN 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram
<TEXT>
<P>
   PORT CHARLOTTE, Fla. _ Outfielder Ruben Mateo has stumbled on a
revolutionary new dietary supplement, more powerful than the
androstenedione Mark McGwire was taking during his record-breaking
home- run season.
</P>
<P>
   The chocolate chip cookie.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's true,'' Mateo said yesterday, standing in a clubhouse
that soon could be swept by a cookie craze. ``I started eating a
couple of cookies, and that's when I started to hit. Now I eat two
every day. I'm going to keep doing it during the season.
</P>
<P>
   Mateo smiled and held up two fingers.
</P>
<P>
   ``Every day, two cookies,'' Mateo said. ``I'm going to break the
hitting record. I'm going to hit in 162 straight games.''
</P>
<P>
   Mateo ate two more yesterday, then went 1-for-3 with his fifth
home run in the Rangers' 7-6 victory over the Philadelphia
Phillies. The Cookie Monster has now hit safely in seven
consecutive games since going on the cookie craze and is batting
.393 for the spring.
</P>
<P>
   ``Maybe they need to give me a truckload of those things,'' said
second baseman Luis Alicea, who is hitting .214.
</P>
<P>
   The only controversy surrounding the chocolate-chip-hitting
binge is who turned Mateo on to it. Both shortstop Royce Clayton
and manager Johnny Oates claim credit.
</P>
<P>
   ``I walked in one day, saw Ruben eating a salad,'' Oates said.
``I said, `Ruben, you ever have a pulled muscle?' He said, yeah. I
said, `You ever have a pulled fat.' He said no. I told him, `You
better starting eating chocolate chip cookies.''
</P>
<P>
   But Clayton insists that's not the way it happened.
</P>
<P>
   ``We were up in Dunedin \RFla.\S,'' Clayton said. ``He's walking
around with no body fat. I said, `Ruben, you brush up against a
fence, you're going to be out a month. You need to start eating
some cookies.'''
</P>
<P>
   Retorted Oates, ``I was onto this five years ago. I said it to
the replacement players. They actually believed me. I told them,
did eating salad get you to the big leagues?''
</P>
<P>
   Clayton's testimony is made suspect by the fact that he's
hitting just .319, clear proof he's not hitting the chocolate chip
cookies hard enough.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm mixing them in,'' Clayton insisted. ``I'm waiting for the
season to start. It's a veteran move. You can't eat them all down
here, you have to save some for the season.''
</P>
<P>
   Mateo tried to push some off on first baseman Rafael Palmeiro
but so far has failed to get anywhere.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't need chocolate chip cookies,'' Palmeiro insisted. ``I
drink chocolate protein shakes.''
</P>
<P>
   Yummy.
</P>
<P>
   Outfielder Gabe Kapler, sitting next to Palmeiro in the
clubhouse and eating a green apple, was more receptive. Kapler is a
fitness guru with jars of the latest nutritional drinks sitting
above his locker.
</P>
<P>
   But when he heard about Mateo's secret, Kapler said, ``Bring 'em
on, I'll eat them.''
</P>
<P>
   ``What are you talking about, you're hitting .900,'' Palmeiro
said, pointing to Kapler's jar of Triple Whey Shake. ``I need to
get me more of that stuff.''
</P>
<P>
   However, Palmeiro doesn't realize chocolate chip cookies may be
just what the Rangers need to turn the tables on the New York
Yankees in October. Serious investigative reporting has revealed
the Yankees feast on chocolate chip cookies.
</P>
<P>
   ``I can confirm that,'' ex-Yankees player Chad Curtis reported.
``All cookies are big over there. Those guys are always gorging on
cookies. Scott Brosius is the king of all cookie eaters.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll tell you what. For all the serious advances in medical
technology, the Yankees are a throwback to teams of 20 years ago.
They gorge themselves on anything they want to eat.''
</P>
<P>
   ``They do?'' Palmeiro said when hearing this tidbit.
</P>
<P>
   ``Well then, bring on the chocolate chip cookies.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
