<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   BEST ACTOR
</P>
<P>
   Russell Crowe ``The Insider''
</P>
<P>
   Character: Jeffrey Wigand, the real-life tobacco industry
whistle-blower who, with ``60 Minutes'' producer Lowell Bergman,
went public with the truth about nicotine.
</P>
<P>
   Age: 35.
</P>
<P>
   Birthplace: Wellington, New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
   Did you know? He had a TV series in New Zealand at the age of 6.
He gained attention in America after his performance in 1994's
``The Sum of Us.''
</P>
<P>
   Oscar history: His first Academy Award win. No previous
nominations.
</P>
<P>
   Other notable movies: ``Mystery, Alaska'' (1999), ``L.A.
Confidential'' (1997), ``Virtuosity'' (1995), ``The Quick and the
Dead'' (1995), ``The Sum of Us'' (1994), ``Romper Stomper'' (1992).
</P>
<P>
   Upcoming: He plays Maximus in director Ridley Scott's big-budget
``Gladiator,'' scheduled to open May 5. He also stars in Taylor
Hackford's ``Proof of Life.''
</P>
<P>
   Richard Farnsworth ``The Straight Story''
</P>
<P>
   Character: Alvin Straight, the real-life Midwesterner who drove
a tractor on a six-week trip to make amends with his brother.
</P>
<P>
   Age: 79.
</P>
<P>
   Birthplace: Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   Did you know? He was a double for Roy Rogers and other stars of
Westerns and action films. He's the oldest actor ever to be
nominated in this category.
</P>
<P>
   Oscar history: This is his first Oscar win. He was previously
nominated in the supporting category for 1978's ``Comes a
Horseman.''
</P>
<P>
   Other notable movies: ``The Two Jakes'' (1990), ``The Natural''
(1984), ``The Grey Fox'' (1982), ``The Cowboys'' (1972), ``The Life
and Times of Judge Roy Bean'' (1972).
</P>
<P>
   Upcoming: In July, he'll appear in archival footage in TV's
``Anne of Green Gables: The Continuing Story.''
</P>
<P>
   Sean Penn ``Sweet and Lowdown''
</P>
<P>
   Character: Emmet Ray, the 1930s jazz guitarist in Woody Allen's
comedic biopic.
</P>
<P>
   Age: 39.
</P>
<P>
   Birthplace: Burbank, Calif.
</P>
<P>
   Did you know? He skipped college and went directly to the Group
Repertory Theatre of Los Angeles after graduating from Santa Monica
High School. His first appearance: guest on TV's ``Barnaby Jones.''
</P>
<P>
   Oscar history: This is his first Oscar win. He was previously
nominated for 1995's ``Dead Man Walking.''
</P>
<P>
   Other notable movies: ``Being John Malkovich'' (1999), ``The
Thin Red Line'' (1998), ``The Game'' (1997), ``Carlito's Way''
(1993), ``Racing With the Moon'' (1984), ``Fast Times at Ridgemont
High'' (1982).
</P>
<P>
   Upcoming: Portrays Thomas Janes in Kathryn Bigelow's ``The
Weight of Water,'' about a woman researching a double ax murder in
1873 as a tie-in to modern-day slayings. Also appears in Philip
Haas' ``Up at the Villa.''
</P>
<P>
   Kevin Spacey ``American Beauty''
</P>
<P>
   Character: Lester Burnham, the drowning suburbanite who fights
back against his job and domineering wife in former Marietta writer
Alan Ball's dark comedy.
</P>
<P>
   Age: 40.
</P>
<P>
   Birthplace: South Orange, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   Did you know? He was expelled from California's Northridge
Military Academy for throwing a tire at a fellow cadet.
</P>
<P>
   Oscar history: This is his second Oscar win. He won a supporting
trophy for 1995's ``The Usual Suspects.''
</P>
<P>
   Other notable movies: ``L.A. Confidential'' (1997), ``Seven''
(1995), ``Swimming With Sharks'' (1994), ``The Ref'' (1994),
``Glengarry Glen Ross'' (1992).
</P>
<P>
   Upcoming: Plays Michael Lynch in Thaddeus O'Sullivan's Irish
gangster movie ``Ordinary Decent Criminal'' and stars in Mimi
Leder's ``Pay It Forward.''
</P>
<P>
   Denzel Washington ``The Hurricane''
</P>
<P>
   Character: Rubin ``Hurricane'' Carter, the boxer wrongly
imprisoned for roughly 20 years for a triple murder he did not
commit.
</P>
<P>
   Age: 45.
</P>
<P>
   Birthplace: Mount Vernon, N.Y.
</P>
<P>
   Did you know? He made his directing debut with 1999's ``Finding
Fish.''
</P>
<P>
   Oscar history: This is his second Oscar win. He won a supporting
trophy for 1989's ``Glory.'' He was previously nominated for 1992's
``Malcolm X'' and 1987's ``Cry Freedom.''
</P>
<P>
   Other notable movies: ``Courage Under Fire'' (1996), ``Devil in
a Blue Dress'' (1995), ``Philadelphia'' (1993), ``A Soldier's
Story'' (1984).
</P>
<P>
   Upcoming: He plays a high school head football coach in Disney's
made-in-Atlanta film ``Remember the Titans.''
</P>
<P>
   BEST ACTRESS
</P>
<P>
   Annette Bening ``American Beauty''
</P>
