r e BC-MOREBEATTY-QUOTES-LAD     03-27 0258
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MORE </SLUG>
 BEATTY-QUOTES-LADN  
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Warren Beatty, after receiving the Irving Thalberg Memorial
Award: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I thank my profession for giving me freedom and access - the
freedom to live a much fuller life apart from the movies and the
access to get out and get to know the world and then come back and
go back to making movies,'' Beatty said. ``Please forgive me for
not making more of them, I'll try to do better.
</P>
<P>
   ``Thank you so much for encouraging my voice in public affairs.
Please forgive me if I've used it stridently or in fact not often
enough. I'll try to do better.''
</P>
<P>
   But he's ``first, last and always an actor,'' Beatty said. ``My
pride in that is unbounded.''
</P>
<P>
   One of Hollywood's most notorious onetime playboys called his
pregnant wife, best actress nominee Annette Bening, his
``treasure.''
</P>
<P>
   ``She has given me what I value most, her love, and she's given
me Kathlyn and Ben and Isabel and at the moment, this much
anticipated and very loved unnamed being ...''
</P>
<P>
   Beatty said he ``cannot imagine a public circumstance in which
so many affirmations of work and life could converge at one time.
As a screenwriter, I'd never sit still for it.
</P>
<P>
   ``You know, you can't have the husband up here getting this
thing and the wife down there maybe getting that thing and she's
having a baby at the same time. It doens't work.
</P>
<P>
   ``You have to pick one. They'll never believe it. Don't worry, I
don't ever expect another evening like this to be so full.''
</P>
</TEXT>
