<P>
   &UR; NOT JUST ONE OF THE BOYS: HILARY SWANK AND `BOYS DON'T CRY' &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,400 words) Includes a color slide of Hilary Swank with Chloe
Sevigny in a scene from ``Boys Don't Cry.'' &QL; 
 &UR; By IAN SPELLING &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Hilary Swank has done soap opera in ``Beverly Hills 90210,''
shown her athletic prowess in the feature film ``The Next Karate
Kid'' and faced evil in the original film version of ``Buffy the
Vampire Slayer,'' but her latest film is easily her most
challenging _ and has earned her an Oscar as Best Actress of 1999.
``Boys Don't Cry'' casts her as Brandon Teena, nee Teena Brandon, a
woman who disguised herself as a man and began a new life for
herself in small-town Nebraska, until hatred and intolerance
brought this real-life story to a tragic ending. Swank talks with
New York-based free-lance writer Ian Spelling about the film, the
unique challenges of playing a woman playing a man, her own
experiences with intolerance and why she thinks Brandon Teena's
story had to be told. (slugged:
BC-HILARY-SWANK-IN-BOYS-DONT-CRY-STARBEAT-ART-NYTSF, priority code
w, category code e) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MICHAEL CAINE, AMERICAN-STYLE &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,400 words) Includes a color slide of Michael Caine with Tobey
Maguire in a scene from ``The Cider House Rules.'' &QL; 
 &UR; By CINDY PEARLMAN &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; World rights except Chicago &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Michael Caine has never played an American before _ the accent
took him weeks of coaching to master _ but it was worth it to make
``The Cider House Rules,'' he says. The film casts him as a kindly
doctor who runs an orphanage, and also performs abortions on the
side to prevent unwanted children from being born. Caine talks with
Chicago-based free-lance writer Cindy Pearlman about the new film,
the horrendous experiences from his own childhood which drew him to
the role, why he's happier as an actor now that he's aged out of
leading-man roles and why he didn't want to talk about the Oscar
chances for his performance in ``Cider House Rules.'' (slugged:
BC-MICHAEL-CAINE-IN-THE-CIDER-HOUSE-RULES-STARBEAT-ART-NYTSF,
priority code w, category code e) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FACE VALUE: RISING CAINE &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; By RICARDO CASTANEDA &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   In this color cartoon feature from The New York Times Syndicate,
artist Ricardo Castaneda offers an intriguing take on Michael Caine
playing the sympathetic doctor in the upcoming film, ``The Cider
House Rules.''
