r l BC-TECH-LINK28-COX     03-27 0231
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TECH-LINK28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Linking to the best of the Net
 &HT;    By Omar L. Gallaga
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   www.clip2.com _ Many guides to the Internet are sorted by topic
interest _ just ask the folks at Yahoo. Clip2's claim to fame is
that anyone can create a topic on his/her site and enhance it with
images, links and anything else. The topic guides are then sorted
by daily popularity ratings. Clip2 is a place to not only find, but
also create information on the Web.
</P>
<P>
   www.zing.com _ Lots of folks create Web pages just so they can
share scanned-in images with family and friends. Zing.com takes the
hosting out of that by offering a free place to store, share or
print your online photo album. Upload your photos here and you can
even create your own virtual postcards to send through the site.
</P>
<P>
   www.tarantulaplanet.org _ If you've got a hairy spider fetish
(or if you want to just scare your co-workers), visit Tarantula
Planet, an encylopedic site for information about the gargantuan
species of arachnid.
</P>
<P>
   www.rememberit.com _ Absent minded, much? RememberIt.com takes
the guesswork out of forgetting important appointments by sending
you an e-mail reminder that you book ahead of time. Sign-up is
free. Just don't delete those e-mails.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
