<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The kid academy gives: Thumbs up to `Toy Story 2'
 &HT;    By Doug Hamilton
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Buzz and Woody, take a bow. You and your movie, ``Toy
Story 2,'' were among the big winners in our eighth annual Oscar
Junior poll, in which we asked metro Atlanta kids to name their
favorite flicks and stars of 1999.
</P>
<P>
   ``Toy Story 2'' took top honors in the ``best movie'' category.
Buzz and Woody were named ``best buddies,'' and Woody snagged the
prize for ``coolest cartoon character.''
</P>
<P>
   Also finishing strong was ``Star Wars: Episode 1 _The Phantom
Menace,'' which won for ``best special effects.'' Natalie Portman,
who played Queen Amidala in the space adventure, won in the
category of ``best acting by a girl.''
</P>
<P>
   And we can't count the mouse out: ``Stuart Little'' did well,
too, finishing second to ``Toy Story 2'' in the best movie category
by a mere 14 votes.
</P>
<P>
   ``Stuart Little'' also was the No. 2 movie for which you'd most
want a sequel. Only six more kids would rather see a follow-up to
``Star Wars: Episode 1'' than ``Stuart Little.''
</P>
<P>
   Haley Joel Osment, who played the kid who sees ghosts in ``The
Sixth Sense,'' scared up the award for ``best acting by a guy.''
</P>
<P>
   Adam Sandler got goofy in ``Big Daddy'' and won the prize for
``silliest grownup'' by a landslide.
</P>
<P>
   The light-saber duel between Darth Maul and Qui-Gon Jinn in
``Star Wars: Episode 1'' spooked the most voters and was named
``scariest scene.''
</P>
<P>
   Voting in our poll were more than 700 Atlanta area readers,
including 130 who filled out our first-ever online ballot.
</P>
<P>
   (We confess that the vote isn't scientific _ some kids didn't
vote in every category, and we have a sneaking suspicion that some
of you onliners voted more than once.)
</P>
<P>
   Here is a list of the Oscar Junior winners:
</P>
<P>
   Best movie: ``Toy Story 2.''
</P>
<P>
   Best acting by a girl : Natalie Portman in ``Star Wars: Episode
1 _ The Phantom Menace.'' (Portman barely beat ``Inspector
Gadget's'' Michelle Trachtenberg by only 12 votes.)
</P>
<P>
   Best acting by a guy: Haley Joel Osment in ``The Sixth Sense.''
</P>
<P>
   Silliest grown-up: Adam Sandler. (Sandler crushed the
competition. He had 494 votes. Matthew Broderick in ``Inspector
Gadget'' got only 85 votes.)
</P>
<P>
   Coolest cartoon character: Woody in ``Toy Story 2.''
</P>
<P>
   Best special effects: ``Star Wars: Episode 1.''
</P>
<P>
   Best buddies: Woody and Buzz in ``Toy Story 2.''
</P>
<P>
   Scariest scene: Darth Maul and Qui-Gon Jinn duel with light
sabers in ``Star Wars: Episode 1.''
</P>
<P>
   I would most like to see a sequel of: ``Star Wars: Episode 1.''
(So close! ``Stuart Little'' got 165 votes compared to ``Star Wars:
Episode 1's'' 171 votes.)
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
