<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-27 11:07 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9043 &Cx1f; tad-z
r f BC-TVS-SPEAKERS0328-COX     03-27 0475
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TVS-SPEAKERS0328-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Speakers made to blend in
 &HT;    By James Cummings
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ As the television screens in home theater setups
keep getting larger, the speakers for the audio portion of the
systems seem to be getting smaller.
</P>
<P>
   Instead of using massive speakers that sit on the floor, many
home theater enthusiasts are getting full theater sound from
speakers that can be built into walls or set inconspicuously on a
bookshelf.
</P>
<P>
   Morel Ltd., an Israeli company, won an Innovation Award at this
year's Consumer Electronics Show for a grapefruit-sized home
theater satellite speaker designed to blend with modernistic decor.
</P>
<P>
   The Innovation Award committee said, ``The SoundSpot SA-2 is a
uniquely designed two-way surround speaker that provides audiophile
performance from within a small and elegant enclosure.''
</P>
<P>
   Each SoundSpot SA-2 has a separate driver for its 4-inch
midrange and bass speaker and its tweeter. The midrange speaker is
housed in a steel globe, and the tweeter is housed in a separate
compartment attached to the top of the globe.
</P>
<P>
   The steel globes come in sand-roughened silver, black or white
with color-coordinated fabric speaker grill covers.
</P>
<P>
   The speakers are attached to a base that can be set on a shelf
or attached to a wall or ceiling. The SA-2 is magnetically shielded
so speakers also can be placed directly on top of a television.
</P>
<P>
   The speaker base swivels to point the sound in whatever
direction the user chooses. Also available are stands that allow
the speakers to be placed on the floor.
</P>
<P>
   The speakers operate on 15 to 150 watts of power and have a
frequency range of 60 to 22,000 Hz, according to Morel.
</P>
<P>
   A retail outlet in Port Orchard, Wash., is the only store in the
United States that currently carries the SoundSpot SA-2 speakers,
but they can be ordered directly from the company in Israel.
</P>
<P>
   A company spokeswoman said the speakers were being offered at
$616 a pair at the time this article was prepared, but anyone
wishing to purchase must contact the company by mail or e-mail for
an up-to-date quote.
</P>
<P>
   Morel also manufacture less-expensive home theater satellite
speakers in the SoundSpot line as well as subwoofers and center
channel speakers. The company makes car stereo and other home
theater accessories, too.
</P>
<P>
   For more information on Morel products, visit the company's Web
site at www.morel.co.il. The site includes links to contact the
company by e-mail.
</P>
<P>
   The company's mailing address is Morel (IL) Ltd., 17 Hamazmera
St., P.O. Box 712, Ness Ziona 70400, Israel.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Contact James Cummings at 225-2432 or e-mail him at
jamescummings(at)coxohio.com.
</P>
<P>
   THE SOUNDSPOT SA-2 SPEAKERS are fun and functional.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
