and collapse of the liberals means for Vladimir Putin's presidency.
By Patrick E. Tyler. (See also RUSSIA-BUSINESS, moving in `f' news
category.)
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-POLITICS (Jerusalem) _ This is how the morning after Pope
John Paul II's departure looked in Israel: diminished prospects for
peace with Syria, the opening of a criminal investigation into a
leading rabbi and five separate parliament votes of no confidence
in the government. By Deborah Sontag.
</P>
