   MIDEAST-TALKS (Washington) _ More on President Clinton's Sunday
meeting with the Syrian leader Hafez Assad and a look forward to
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak's Tuesday visit to Washington. By
Jane Perlez.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-LAND (Jerusalem) _ Interior Minister Natan Sharansky
orders the return of some land to Israeli Arabs, ruling that an
Israeli town illegally encroached on the land. By Joel Greenberg.
</P>
<P>
   SAUDI-RIGHTS (Cairo, Egypt) _ An Amnesty International report
says human rights abuses, including torture, are widespread in
Saudi Arabia's criminal justice system and that the United States
turns a blind eye to the problem. By Susan Sachs.
</P>
<P>
   FRANCE-POLITICS (Paris) _ Prime Minister Jospin, reeling after
six weeks of missteps, shuffles Cabinet and brings in former Prime
Minister Fabius, who was tried in tainted-blood scandal.  &QL;
</P>
