a little smudgy piece of paper that showed a kid, you know, looking
through this thing, holding his hand up, and you can see the bones.
And it says the see-through X-ray eye device is very simply worked.
It is worked by placing it to your eye, as shown in diagram A, and
then holding your hand up to the light, as shown by diagram B. Then
if the light is properly adjusted, one will see the bones through
the eyepiece marked C in diagram D. End of instructions.
</P>
