court in Boston Monday and Tuesday. Amgen, the industry leader, is
suing Transkaryotic Therapies, or TKT, contending that TKT's
company's production of Epogen, a genetically engineered form of
protein used by kidney dialysis patients, violates Amgen's patents.
The stakes are huge: Epogen is Amgen's top-selling drug, generating
$4 billion in annual sales. More important, the case will touch on
one of the fundamental questions of the biotechnology age _ just
how far patents can extend to cover a substance found in nature. By
Andrew Pollack.
