<HEADER>
A9197 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u v BC-HEARST-NEWS-BUDGET-HN     03-27 0239
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HEARST-NEWS-BUDGET-HNS </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Monday, March 27, 2000 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Editors &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service will file the following for Tuesday. If
you have questions, please call Susie McBee or Tim Spence at
202-298-6920.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (The ``HNS'' tag appears in all sluglines.)
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-FINANCE (Washington) _ Vice President Al Gore and Texas
Gov. George W. Bush clash over Gore's proposal to ``break the link
between money and political influence'' with a $7.1 billion
endowment to pay for House and Senate campaigns. Bush charges that
the plan would be ``a taxpayer-financed government takeover'' of
the campaigns. Experts see little chance of an overhaul this year.
By STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
