<P>
   217 MILLION TONS OF WASTE
</P>
<P>
   In 1997 Americans generated about 217 million tons of trash and
garbage, known as municipal solid waste, and recycled or composted
60.7 million tons. Here is a scorecard, by categories:
</P>
<P>
   ...........................................................Percent
</P>
<P>
   ....................................Tons.................of
total ............Percent recycled
</P>
<P>
   Material.........................generated.........waste
stream.....or composted
</P>
<P>
   Paper and paperboard......83.8
million......38.6.................41.7
</P>
<P>
   Yard trimmings...............27.7
million......12.8.................41.4
</P>
<P>
   Food..............................21.9
million......10.1...................2.6
</P>
<P>
   Plastics..........................21.5
million........9.9...................5.2
</P>
<P>
   Metals............................16.6
million.......7.7.................39.1
</P>
<P>
   Rubber, leather, textiles...14.8
million.......6.8.................12.8
</P>
<P>
   Glass.............................12.0
million.......5.5.................24.3
</P>
<P>
   Wood.............................11.6
million.......5.3...................5.1
</P>
<P>
   Other...............................7.0
million.......3.3.................20.2
</P>
<P>
   Source: Environmental Protection Agency, ``Characterization of
Municipal Solid Waste in the United States, 1998 Update.''
</P>
<P>
   Categories do not include certain industrial wastes, sewage
sludge, automobile bodies or construction and demolition debris.
</P>
<P>
   Some Internet sites with further information on composting and
recycling in America include:
</P>
