<SLUG> BC-TRAVEL-SHOPPING-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SHOPPING AROUND: SPRING SKIING  
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following material from The New York Times
Syndicate is for use by WAY TO GO! clients. Nonsubscribers can use
this article only by special arrangement. For purchase information,
see end of text. ONE COLOR SLIDE, AVAILABLE FREE OF CHARGE, CAN BE
SENT TO YOU ELECTRONICALLY. 
 &HT;    
 (PLEASE NOTE: This article has been transmitted twice _ into the
``t'' travel news and ``l'' lifestyle news files.)  
 &HT;    
 By EVERETT POTTER  
 &HT;    Spring on the slopes means balmy weather and bargains. That is
especially true this spring, when many ski areas are trying to make
up for a rocky start that left them high and dry. Now they have the
snow, but they also have too many empty hotel rooms and condos.
 &HT;    Smart skiers and snowboarders should be on the lookout for even
deeper discounts than normal. Prices will dip around the end of
March and then fall off in April, with reductions that range from
20 percent to 70 percent off high-season prices.
 &HT;    To find the cheapest airline seats, plan to fly to hub cities
like Denver and Salt Lake City, which are served by many carriers.
 &HT;    Spring skiing is also perfect for last-minute skiers _ those who
commit only when the snow seems right. Here's a look at some
packages for Spring 2000. Prices are per person, based on double
occupancy.
 &HT;    From March 26 to April 14, Ascutney Mountain Resort (Rt. 44,
P.O. Box 699, Brownsville, Vt. 05037; 800-243-0011;
www.ascutney.com) is offering a ``Two-Day Value Season Vacation''
for $73 per person and a ``Three-Day Mini-Vacation'' for $69 per
person. The packages include lift tickets and slope-side suite
lodging, with complimentary access to the Sports and Fitness Center
and the tubing area in the Resort Village.
 &HT;    Day-trippers note that from April 3 through seasons' end, adult
lift tickets cost $28.
 &HT;    Okemo Mountain Resort (77 Okemo Ridge Road, Ludlow, Vt. 05149;
800-78-OKEMO; www.okemo.com) has a midweek ``Ski &AMP; Stay Package''
from $45 per person, per day, starting April 2. It's $89.50 on
weekends. All packages include lift tickets and slope-side
condominium accommodations.
 &HT;    At Sun Valley (Sun Valley, Idaho, 83353; 800-786-8259;
www.sunvalley.com), the spring ski package runs from April 2 to 23.
The cost is $56 per person, per night, for lodging at the Sun
Valley Resort and a one-day lift pass.
 &HT;    Keystone Resort (P.O. Box 38, Keystone, Colo. 80435;
800-404-3535; www.keystoneresort.com) is offering 50 percent off
lodging in March and April, but skiers need to book the package 21
days prior to their arrival. From April 2 through April 22, prices
start at just $88 a night.
 &HT;    Keystone has also teamed up with neighboring A-Basin in May and
June. For $59 per person/per night, skiers can stay at Keystone and
get a free one-day lift ticket at A-Basin. The deal is good through
June 15.
 &HT;    Steamboat (2305 Mt. Werner Circle, Steamboat Springs, Colo.
80487; 800-922-2722; www.steamboat-ski.com) is offering a ``Last
Chance Snowsaver'' from April 9 to 16 that starts at $210 per
person based on double occupancy. It includes four nights' motel
accommodations and a three-day lift ticket. For $334, skiers get
six nights' condo accommodation and a five-day lift ticket, based
on quad occupancy.
 &HT;    They also have short ``Breakaway Packages.'' These include two
nights' lodging and a two-day lift ticket. One child, age 12 or
under, per paid adult, can ski for free. From April 1 to 8, the
rate is $136 per person; from April 9 to 16, $106.
 &HT;    Northstar-at-Tahoe (P.O. Box 129, Truckee, Calif. 96160;
800-GO-NORTH; www.skinorthstar.com) has a ``Spring Madness''
package from April 2 until closing day, which is projected to be
May 1. The two-night package is priced from $74.50 plus tax, per
person, per night, in a studio condominium and includes an all-day
lift ticket. Guests have access to the Swim and Racquet Club. A
two-night stay is required.
 &HT;    Winter Park (239 Winter Park Drive, Winter Park, Colo. 80482;
800-729-5813; www.skiwinterpark.com) has a variety of lodging deals
to tempt late-season skiers. For example, Destination West homes
and condos at Winter Park has the following package: Starting April
3, stay three consecutive nights and the fourth night is free. At
the Vintage Hotel, a studio hotel room that sleeps up to four
people is $135 per night for a two-night minimum stay. And at the
Winter Park Mountain Lodge, hotel rooms are $75 a night.
 &HT;    Telluride (565 Mountain Village Blvd., Telluride, Colo. 81435;
800-854-3062; www.telski.com) has the ``Ski Free &AMP; More'' package
from March 31 to April 8. Skiers can choose from a full day of free
skiing, a complimentary clinic with Telluride's Ski &AMP; Snowboard
School, a free lunch on the mountain or a free, half-day of child
care for each night spent in participating properties in Telluride.
Prices start at $53 per person, per night, based on minimum
occupancy.
 &HT;    Moguls Ski and Snowboard Tours (4876 Sterling Drive, Boulder,
Colo. 80301; 800-666-4857; www.skimoguls.com) has air/hotel/lift
ticket deals to mountains around North America. The following
include round-trip airfare, five nights' accommodation, transfers
and four days of lift tickets. Prices are per person and are based
on travel from East Coast cities.
 &HT;    
 &HT;    PRICE.............DESTINATION..............DATES
 &HT;    $879..........Whistler/Blackcomb.......April 3 to 30
 &HT;    $819.............Jackson Hole.........through April 3
 &HT;    $765..............Park City........April 2 to April 16
 &HT;    (The last trip is based on quad occupancy in a two-bedroom
unit.)
 &HT;    
 &HT;    Other tour operators have similar offerings. Contact:
