<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUCHANAN-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WILL PAT BUCHANAN'S MESSAGE FIND APPROVAL
 IN ARIZONA? 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service
 clients)  
 By RUBEN NAVARETTE  
 (EDITORS: STORY WILL ALSO MOVE IN THE
 ``A'' CATEGORY.) 
 c.2000 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   CAMBRIDGE, Mass. _ With John McCain off the bus and back in the
Senate, and George W. Bush back in Texas and off to try to avenge
his father's 1992 defeat, reporters with time on their hands are
musing about whether Bush can woo McCain voters.
</P>
<P>
   If so, Bush had better hurry. Someone else has his eye on them.
Patrick J. Buchanan, the fearless storyteller, is known for
stirring the pot, challenging convention and going against the
grain. Now pursuing the presidential nomination of the Reform
Party, Buchanan is targeting the followers of McCain, who built a
presidential campaign on stirring the pot, challenging convention,
