   BBO-JAPAN _ The baseball season won't open in Cincinnati, as it
always used to, but rather in the Far East. For the first time,
regular-season games will be played in Japan. The Cubs and Mets
play Wednesday and Thursday, with the games starting at 5 a.m. EST.
