to the Final Four and will head into the national semifinals next
weekend as the favorite to win it all. The road to Indianapolis
hasn't been easy for the Spartans, who have had to come from behind
in the second half of their last three tournament wins. With an
experienced lineup led by senior guard Mateen Cleaves and the
memory of last year's Final Four loss fresh on their minds, the
Spartans look to win two more games for their first national title
since 1979. (Arey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
