thinking it was the KKK,'' the 20-year-old black woman said. ``I
was terrified. I thought of all kinds of stuff: churches being
burned, bottles being thrown through windows, houses being set on
fire.'' Holmes was stunned when authorities charged three of her
closest neighbors, including Richland City Council member Roy
``Pete'' Cobb, with the Feb. 16 cross burning. (Davis, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
