u e BC-TV-DAWSON-SPINOFF-NYT     03-27 0789
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-DAWSON-SPINOFF-NYTR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`YOUNG AMERICANS' TO LAUNCH FROM `DAWSON'S CREEK' 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: N.C., Md.)  (lb) 
 By ALLISON BALLARD   
 Morning Star, Wilmington, N.C.   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WILMINGTON, N.C. _ ``Dawson's Creek'' is now filming the finale
for its third season. In addition to the usual cliff-hanging
suspense that producers plan for fans, there is a twist in the
works _ a spinoff series that will premiere this summer on the WB
network. Producers hope the fans of one high school drama will
start following another.
</P>
<P>
   The star of the new show, Rodney Scott, has come to Wilmington,
where ``Dawson's Creek'' is filmed, to appear in three of Creek's
last four episodes this season before moving on to ``Young
Americans.''
</P>
<P>
   Spinoffs, in general, have a spotty track record. Consider some
recent examples: Jennifer Love Hewitt's ``Time of Your Life,'' an
offshoot of Fox's ``Party of Five,'' is facing cancellation, and
``Ally,'' the 30-minute ``Ally McBeal'' spinoff, didn't make it
through the season.
</P>
<P>
   On the other hand, some spinoffs have stood the test of time;
``The Jeffersons,'' ``Maude,'' ``Laverne &AMP; Shirley'' and ``Rhoda''
are all television classics. And ``Frasier'' consistently does well
in ratings.
</P>
<P>
   Most spinoffs use established characters to start the new show,
but that is not the case for ``Young Americans.'' ``Melrose Place''
had a similar start from ``Beverly Hills, 90210'' _ with an
introduced character starring in the new show. This is technically
called a cross promotion, said series creator, Steven Antin. ``It's
not a spinoff.''
</P>
<P>
   But no matter what you call it, Scott may have the potential
star power to get ``Americans'' off to a good start. After moving
to Los Angeles two years ago, Scott not only landed the series
pilot but he also had the role of David Cassidy in ``Come On, Get
Happy: The Partridge Family Story'' and was a guest star on
``X-Files.'' He was also named as a fresh face in Teen People.
</P>
<P>
   ``Young Americans'' is set at a New England boarding school _
just a few fictional hours' drive from Dawson's Capeside. Antin got
the idea for the series while driving in New England. At a gas
station, he spotted prep school boys flirting with some local
girls.
</P>
<P>
   The pilot for the series was filmed last April. It wasn't picked
up for this season but studio executives had the idea to do a cross
promotion with ``Dawson's Creek,'' which is also on WB.
</P>
<P>
   ``I said `I have not heard a better idea,''' Antin said. ``I am
a big fan of `Dawson's Creek.' And what better platform to launch
`Young Americans?'''
</P>
<P>
   Scott's character (Will Krudski) is a long-lost friend of Joshua
Jackson's character (Pacey). Because his home life is troubling,
Will decides to pay a visit to Capeside. There he meets the
Dawson's Creek buddies _ and develops a strong friendship with
Meredith Monroe's character (Andie McPhee).
</P>
<P>
   Exactly how close, Monroe said, fans will have to wait and see.
Scott filmed his final Creek appearance last week. It included a
scene where he tells Andie he is leaving Capeside.
</P>
<P>
   The cross promotion continues with a possible appearance by the
Creek cast on the new show _ maybe Joshua or Andie will make that
two-hour drive to the boarding school, Raley Academy, that is the
main setting of ``Young Americans,'' Monroe said.
</P>
<P>
   The boarding school ``is pretty much high school without parents
_ and no uniforms,'' Scott said.
</P>
<P>
   The story line of the new series has a lot of popular themes _
blue-blooded rich kids vs. local townies, a young men's school
across the river from a young women's school, and coming of age in
a difficult situation.
</P>
<P>
   He said the show is a little racy. ``It is very edgy,'' he said.
``It's more like an HBO series.''
</P>
<P>
   Like many actors on ``Dawson's Creek,'' Scott, 22, will be an
adult playing the role of a high school student, but that doesn't
bother him.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you get older there is, supposedly, a maturity that goes
with it _ and that makes it easier to handle the situation and the
long work days,'' he said. ``And you've been through all that with
high school.''
</P>
<P>
   Scott said the opportunity to work with the Creek cast and crew
was a great experience.
</P>
<P>
   Wilmington and Charlotte are being considered as possible
filming locations, but Baltimore is the most likely locale for the
production, said a publicist for the show.
</P>
<P>
   About half of the pilot episode needs to be reshot and then the
cast will start filming the series. A definite air date has not
been set, but fans should look for ``Young Americans'' beginning in
June.
</P>
<P>
   (Allison Ballard writes for the Morning Star in Wilmington,
N.C., which is part of the New York Times Regional Newspaper
Group.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
