success, Yosemite National Park, the country's most popular
playground, will be returned to a wilder, less traveled condition,
with major reductions in parking spaces, roads and bridges, the
introduction of shuttle buses and the elimination of buildings and
other structures in the park. In the second plan in two years to
reduce the blight of pollution and overcrowding, Bruce Babbitt, the
secretary of the interior, outlined a blueprint here Monday that
would make major changes in the ways visitors can enjoy the park.
By Evelyn Nieves.
