   BANKONE-DIMON (New York) _ Bank One, rocked by a series of
management blunders and earnings shortfalls following one of the
biggest mergers in banking history, named James Dimon, 44, one of
the most highly regarded executives on Wall Street, as the
beleaguered company's new chairman and chief executive. By Timothy
L. O'Brien.
