   HERE ARE TONIGHT'S OTHER REGULAR FEATURES:
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Major stock market averages moved lower
Monday, dragged down by declines in financial service and bank
stocks and by a big decline in Microsoft, which slumped on reports
that the software company remains far from an agreement that would
settle the government's antitrust lawsuit. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved.)
</P>
<P>
   LEESON-AD-COLUMN (London) _ Nicholas Leeson, the rogue stock
trader who caused the collapse of Britain's oldest merchant bank,
Barings PLC, is appearing in a campaign that promotes a Swedish
dot-com stock trading company. It may sound bizarre, but the
commercial's creators said bizarre was very much the point.
</P>
<P>
   (Column has moved.)
</P>
<P>
   BIZGLANCE (Undated) _ Digest of the day's financial stories.
</P>
