<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-SPORTS-BUDGET- </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following sports
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
March 27 and thereafter. For questions about stories, resends or
inquiries, call Patrick Hipes at (818) 713-3602. 
 
 
BKC-MICHIGANST (Flint, Mich.) _ A feature on Michigan State men's
basketball players Mateen Cleaves, Morris Peterson and Charlie
Bell, all three from Flint, Mich. As an advance to Saturday's Final
Four. 
By Karen Crouse. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BKN-LAKERNOTES (Los Angeles) _ A Los Angeles Lakers notebook. 
By Howard Beck. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-DODGERS-ELSTER (Vero Beach, Fla.) _ Kevin Elster spent last
season hanging out by the pool. Now, he'll be the starting
shortstop for the Los Angeles Dodgers, just 20 minutes from the
Pacific Ocean. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-DODGERS-NOTEBOOK _ Will not file. 
 
 
BBA-ANGELS-NOTEBOOK (Tucson, Ariz.) _ An Anaheim Angels notebook. 
By Joe Haakenson/San Gabriel Valley Tribune. (Will move on the
``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBO-PARENT (Peoria, Ariz.) _ After 10 years playing in the major
leagues, Mark Parent is trying his hand at a new career. He's the
first-year manager of the Single-A Lancaster JetHawks of the
California League. 
By Kevin Modesti. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
HKN-MCHALE-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Matt McHale's weekly NHL column. 
By Matt McHale. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
