   FOLD
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-POLITICS (Jerusalem) _ And so Pope John Paul II flew away
and took his positive glow with him. This is how the morning after
looked in Israel: diminished prospects for peace with Syria, the
opening of a politically explosive criminal investigation of a
leading rabbi and five separate Parliament votes of no confidence
in the government. By Deborah Sontag. (The story has moved in ``i''
news file; will be updated.) 1,400 words.
