<HEADLINE>
SOME TRAVEL DEALS  
 (FOR RELEASE SUNDAY, APRIL 2) 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 By JANET PIORKO   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Italy's Lakes &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Italiatour, the tour division of Alitalia, has packages to the
lake district of northern Italy that start at $1,199 a person,
double occupancy, from New York, Newark or Boston. The price
includes round-trip flights to Milan, seven nights at the Hotel
Metropole in Bellaggio, with service charges and VAT, breakfast and
dinner daily and seven-day rental of a small manual-transmission
car with insurance and unlimited mileage. Travel must be completed
by June 14.
</P>
<P>
   From Friday through May 31, the company also has a package to
Tuscany including air fare from New York, Newark or Boston to
Florence or Pisa, six hotel nights and a six-day car rental
starting at $1,099 a person at the Hotel Leon Bianco in San
Gimignano. Information and reservations: (800) 845-3365. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Weekend In Manhattan &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Regal U.N. Plaza Hotel has a weekend ``Top of the World''
rate of $179 a room on Friday and Saturday through May 31 that
includes car service to the theater district or Fifth Avenue
shopping and either a full American breakfast for two or a
two-for-one Champagne and lobster brunch on Sundays (except Easter)
for $56 plus tax and tip. The room tax of 13\ percent plus $2 is
extra. Arrangements for the car service must be made the night
before.
</P>
<P>
   The 427-room hotel is at 44th Street and First Avenue, with a
health club that has an indoor heated pool. For more information
and reservations, call (800) 222-8888 or go to the hotel's Web site
at www.unplaza.com. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Ecuador Off Season &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Ecuadorean company Metropolitan Touring has extended its low
season for the Amazon and the Galapagos to the Thanksgiving and
pre-Christmas period. The low season now encompasses Nov. 21 to
Dec. 20 as well as March 16 to June 14 and Sept. 1 to Oct. 31.
Galapagos cruises are reduced 10 percent on the Isabela II, 15
percent on the Santa Cruz flagship and 20 percent on the Delfin
hotel and yacht program.
</P>
<P>
   The cost of three-, four- and seven-night programs ranges from
$555 to $1,290 a person on the Delfin, $1,140 to $2,660 on the
Isabela II and from $764 to $3,080 on the Santa Cruz. In addition,
rates are lowered at the Flotel Orellana, a floating hotel in the
Cuyabeno Wildlife Reserve, and at wilderness lodges there. They
range from $325 a person, double occupancy, for two nights, to $590
for five nights. Reservations: (800) 527-2500. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Sydney Sojourn &QL; 
 &QL;
