<P>
   (NYT26) HOLLYWOOD -- March 27, 2000 -- OSCARS-5 -- Warren
Beatty, the recipient of the Irving G. Thalberg Award for a
lifetime of achievement in the movie business, with presenter Jack
Nicholson at the Shrine Auditorium on Sunday night following the
Academy Awards. In accepting the award, Beatty paid tribute to his
fellow actors, to the friends who led him through his wilder single
years and to his wife, and made reference to his recent flirtation
with a campaign for president. ``If you had your choice and, say,
could have the Thalberg Award or, oh, the White House, I'd stick
with this,'' he said. (Monica Almeida/The New York Times)
</P>
