   (NYT1) OFF KEY LARGO, Fla. -- March 27, 2000 -- SCI-CORAL-REEFS
-- Penny Bailey observes tiny eggs and sperm erupting from a
portion of the coral reefs along the Florida Keys in late
September, 1999. The federal government has issued a long-term plan
to save coral reefs along the coast of the United States and its
territories, setting aside many sites as ecological preserves over
the next 10 years. (Bob Kane, Monroe County Tourism Council/The New
York Times)
