   (NYT39) NEW YORK -- March 27, 2000 -- NY-FOSTER-CARE-3 --
Thousands of young adults in New York City's foster care system
have been pushed out of the system in recent years, forced as young
as 18 to fend for themselves. Sherrell F., with her daughter,
Tamara, is apartment-hunting, because in August, when she turns 18,
she will be discharged from the foster home in the Bronx where she
has been living. She expects another child in June. (James
Estrin/The New York Times)
