<P>
   (NYT31) DARLINGTON, Md. -- March 27, 2000 -- SCI-DIABETES-DRUG-1
-- The removal of the diabetes drug Rezulin by the Food and Drug
Administration last week brought anger, confusion and a stream of
questions from doctors and patients alike. Frank Hopkins, a
diabetic who raises racehorses, is upset about the removal of the
drug from the market because it greatly improved his health. ``I
think the number of people who have received a negative reaction is
so minimal, so why should the rest of us have to suffer?'' he
asked. (Marty Katz/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
